As of the 2010 census, there were 757 people living in the CDP: 386 male and 371 female. 301 were 19 years old or younger, 180 were ages 20–34, 129 were between the ages of 35 and 49, 86 were between 50 and 64, and the remaining 61 were aged 65 and above. The median age was 24.0 years.

The racial makeup of the CDP was 99.1% [[Race (United States Census)|American Indian]], 0.1% [[Race (United States Census)|White]], and 0.8% [[Race (United States Census)|two or more races]].  0.7% of the population were [[Race (United States Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Race (United States Census)|Latino]] of any race.

There were 189 households in the CDP, 148 family households (78.3%) and 41 non-family households (21.7%), with an average household size of 4.01. Of the family households, 74 were married couples living together, while there were 25 single fathers and 49 single mothers; the non-family households included 34 adults living alone: 20 male and 14 female.

The CDP contained 260 housing units, of which 189 were occupied and 71 were vacant.<ref name="GR2">{{Cite web |title=American FactFinder: Low Mountain CDP, Arizona |url=https://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/1600000US0442590 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://archive.today/20200213092528/https://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/1600000US0442590 |archive-date=February 13, 2020 |access-date=December 19, 2016 |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]}}</ref>

